  "texts": [
    "The weights are readily interpreted: w i = 0.05 means that 5% of the total portfolio value is held in asset i, and w k = -0.01 means that we hold a short position in asset k, with value 1% of the total portfolio value.",
    "The dollar value of asset i held is V w i, where V is the total portfolio value, assumed to be positive.",
    "We denote the weight for the cash account, i.e., our cash value divided by the portfolio value, as c. If c is negative, it represents a loan.",
    "When c > 0 we say the portfolio is diluted with cash; when c < 0, the portfolio is margined.",
    "The dollar value of the cash account is V c."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}